# z Skill — Handoff Entrypoint: epic-update

This session was started via `CONTINUE_SESSION` with `forceWorkflow="z-epic-update"`.
The host has **already** validated the `<z-handoff type="work-complete">`
sentinel at the top of this prompt and parsed its typed metadata into
`session.handoffContext` (issue #695).

## Your task

1. Treat the `<z-handoff type="work-complete">` block in this prompt body as
   the session SSOT. The host verified its structure — you do not re-parse.
2. **Skip `local:z` phases 0–4** — the implementation session already shipped
   the PR. Your only job is to reflect that completion back into the parent
   epic.
3. Post the block's `## Summary` (1–3 lines of behavior-level description) plus
   `## PR` link as a comment on the parent epic issue.
4. Update the parent epic's body checklist: flip the line for the just-merged
   subissue from `[ ]` to `[x]`.
5. Inspect `## Remaining Epic Checklist`:
   - If all subissues are complete AND the Epic Done gate (see
     `using-epic-tasks/reference/github.md` or `reference/jira.md`) passes,
     close the epic.
   - Otherwise, print the remaining subissue list to the user and stop. **Do
     not** automatically emit Handoff #1 for the next subissue
     (using-z §Protocol Rules #3 — no auto-chain).

## Forbidden

- Re-examining the epic spec or redesigning scope — that was settled when the
  epic was created.
- Marking an incomplete subissue as done.
- Automatically chaining into the next subissue's Handoff #1. The user must
  manually kick off the next subissue with `$z <subissue-url>`.

> Hop-budget enforcement (per-session limit of 1 auto-handoff) is issue #697
> scope — this prompt only guides the default, non-chained behavior.
